[I] Universal image viewer

[T] FIM (Fbi IMproved) is a universal image viewer inspired by GNU/Linux
[T] concepts. It is a highly customizable and scriptable image viewer for users
[T] who are comfortable with software like the VIM text editor or the Mutt mail
[T] user agent. It can display in full screen and you control it using the
[T] keyboard.

[U] https://www.nongnu.org/fbi-improved/

[A] Michele Martone
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

